2 section 198f(2) of the corporations act provides: "a person who has ceased to be a director of a company may inspect the books of the company (including its financial records) at all reasonable times for the purposes of a legal proceeding: (a) to which the person is a party; or (b) that the person proposes in good faith to bring; or (c) that the person has reason to believe will be brought against them.